                <head>No. 535.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-09-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 20, 1887</date>. (Received October
                        1.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 266.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit herewith, for the
                    information of the Department, two copies,<note n="*" xml:id="d535fn1">Not
                        published.</note> in the Dutch text, of the speech pronounced by His Majesty
                    the King on the opening of the session of the States-General on the 19th
                    instant.</p>
                <p>It will be seen that His Majesty, after thanking the people for the loyalty and
                    devotion shown on the occasion of the celebration of the seventieth anniversary
                    of his birth, expressed the hope that the constitutional revision bill would be
                    sanctioned by the chambers.</p>
                <p>He declared his relations to be most satisfactory with all foreign powers, and
                    expressed satisfaction at the condition of the army and navy, as well as the
                    finances of the country.</p>
                <p>He announced that measures would be submitted for the consideration of the
                    chambers tending to advance the agricultural and commercial interests of the
                    country.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Isaac Bell, Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
